00:23:08,930 --> 00:23:12,852
is making quick iterative updates to your game to improve it.

481
00:23:13,393 --> 00:23:14,453
And when I say iterate,

482
00:23:14,613 --> 00:23:17,615
I do not mean releasing planned DLC content.

483
00:23:17,915 --> 00:23:19,657
That's not really iterative,

484
00:23:19,737 --> 00:23:21,578
that's just a slow.

485
00:23:22,117 --> 00:23:26,218
continual form of pre-launch production.

486
00:23:27,298 --> 00:23:30,619
I mean actually making small, frequent changes to your game

487
00:23:31,059 --> 00:23:33,380
in response to player feedback and behavioral data

488
00:23:33,640 --> 00:23:35,880
to slowly improve the game over time.

489
00:23:37,081 --> 00:23:38,221
This might seem obvious,

490
00:23:38,401 --> 00:23:40,281
like yes, that's what iterating a game is,

491
00:23:40,761 --> 00:23:44,182
but many AAA games still spend millions of dollars

